IOVIO Guardrails Documentation (v0.12)
This document outlines the mandatory standards for test automation within the IOVIO framework. Adherence to these guidelines ensures codebase consistency, script reliability, and framework compatibility.

1. Keyword Management & Architecture
Core Shared Assets: All globally reusable keywords (such as login procedures, browser setup, etc.) are centrally located in ../resources/common_keywords.robot.
Area-Specific Keywords: When generating new custom keywords for a specific feature or section, they must be stored in a dedicated resource file following the naming convention {area}_keywords.robot (e.g., checkout_keywords.robot, billing_keywords.robot).
Dependency Chain: Every {area}_keywords.robot file must explicitly import common_keywords.robot so that it inherits all foundational reusable assets.
No Local Keywords: Do not define local keywords within individual test suites. Rely entirely on the designated resource files to maintain a single source of truth.

2. Suite Configuration (Settings Section)
Every test suite must strictly adhere to the following *** Settings *** block structure:
Resource Links: Must point to the relevant {area}_keywords.robot file for that suite's domain (which inherently provides access to common_keywords.robot), or directly to common_keywords.robot if no area-specific keywords are required.
Suite Setup: Must be explicitly defined as UI Login Via JWT.

3. UI Interaction & Validation
Navigation: When interacting with the navigation tab, prioritize using the LaunchApp keyword instead of using ClickText.
Visibility Handling: Do not assume elements are immediately interactable. If a field is nested, collapsed, or hidden, scripts must include explicit navigation steps (e.g., clicking "Details" or expanding panels) to expose the element before interaction.
Element Selection: Do not include an asterisk (*) when selecting mandatory elements, even if the asterisk is visibly displayed in the UI next to the element name.
Header Validation: The keyword VerifyPageHeader is strictly prohibited.

4. Text Input Handling (TypeText)
Parameter Restrictions: The clear=True argument is incompatible with QWord/QForce and is explicitly prohibited. Scripts containing this parameter will fail or result in unpredictable behavior.
Clearing Fields: To clear an input field (e.g., for negative testing), pass the ${EMPTY} variable as the value.
Example: TypeText First Name ${EMPTY}
